President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 25, 2013, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. The proclamation aims to strengthen the bonds between Greece and the United States, recognizing the enduring contributions of Greek Americans to American society. It also highlights the shared principles of democracy between the two nations and the importance of respecting differences and moving forward with common purpose. The proclamation congratulates Greece on the 192nd anniversary of its independence and pledges continued solidarity as the country works to rebuild its economy. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.